727040f-b.title: Queens: Jamaica Avenue - 151st Street
727040f-b.text:
Jamaica Ave., south side, between 151st and 152nd Streets, show-
ing in center of view a three story frame structure known as the
Burdet house. Eugene L. Armbruster states that an individual named
Golder conducted a feed store here. This source also gives as a
resident, one Miller. Mrs. Jackson, wife of Dr. Oscar Jackson, was
the 1ast owner.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

725910f-a.title: Queens: Jamaica Avenue - 151st Street
725910f-a.text:
Jamaica Avenue, south side, between 151st and 152nd
Streets, showing an old frame house in the center of the
block, in rear of a brick building which fronts on Jamaica
Avenue. TThe view is from 152nd Street, across a clearance.
In the background is the Montgomery Ward building.
P. L. Sperr  July 21, 1931
NO REPRODUCTIONS
Views 1,2
